*** '''Juna:''' Tell me... a story...
*** {{tact|initial}}
** {{topt|Tell me a new story.}}
*** '''Player:''' Tell me a new story.
*** '''Juna:''' I have already told you my story, and you have not told me yours!
*** '''Juna:''' Tell me... a story...
*** {{tact|initial}}
* {{topt|Not now.}}
** '''Player:''' Not now.
** {{tact|end}}

===Random stories===
* {{trandom}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Animal Magnetism]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so Ava's devices can retrieve ammunition for me when I'm ranging, using the power of the magnet and the undead chicken.
** '''Juna:''' A magnet and an undead chicken? Really?
** '''Player:''' It's useful.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Another Slice of H.A.M.]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and the Dorgeshuun city is now connected to Keldagrim by a rapid train line.
** '''Juna:''' I am always glad to hear tales of the Dorgeshuun.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Ascent of Arceuus]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and with the device destroyed, the people of Arceuus were safe.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[At First Light]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... at the end of the day, I wonder what happened to Fox's equipment...
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Below Ice Mountain]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... after Willow betrayed me, I managed to defeat the guardian. Then I found the Imcando city of Camdozaal!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Beneath Cursed Sands]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... but Pharaoh Kemesis agreed to begin preparations to reopen Menaphos.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Between a Rock...]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... I had to be shot out of a cannon into a rock! But finally I banished the spirit of the rock and Dondakan could mine his gold.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Big Chompy Bird Hunting]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... Poor Rantz was so clumsy he couldn't shoot anything!  {{Sic}} But I managed to kill the Chompy Bird.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Biohazard]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So it turned out there was no plague after all!
** '''Juna:''' Deception of the people by their rulers is a terrible thing.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Black Knights' Fortress]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So in the end the Black Knights were defeated by cabbage!
** '''Juna:''' One should never underestimate the uses of the vegetables of Guthix.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Bone Voyage]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and that's how I got the archaeologists to Fossil Island!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Cabin Fever]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So I holed the enemy ship with another cannon shot, and the Adventurous sailed triumphantly into Mos Le'Harmless!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Children of the Sun]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and that's how I stopped the murder of the Teokan of Ralos!
** '''Juna:''' I have no knowledge of this Ralos you speak of. How curious...
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Client of Kourend]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... but Veos had no idea what was going on. He'd been controlled remotely by his mysterious client the whole time!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Clock Tower]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So it was I who repaired the clock tower.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Cold War]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so I told Larry about the penguins' plot!
** '''Juna:''' The paranoia and ambition of the penguins' leaders will not serve their people well.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Cook's Assistant]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and in the end I found all the ingredients, so the Duke of Lumbridge had a birthday cake after all.
** '''Juna:''' Ah, a happy ending. It would not be good for such an anniversary to go unmarked.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Contact!]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and after I'd defeated the giant scarab, the High Priest gave me a reward lamp to teach me more combat skills.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Corsair Curse]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... where Captain Tock thanked me profusely for solving the mysterious 'curse' and killing the traitor.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Creature of Fenkenstrain]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... But in the end I stopped Fenkenstrain from continuing his horrible experiments.
** '''Juna:''' With the power to create life comes responsibility. I see that Fenkenstrain was not up to the task.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Current Affairs]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and that's how I was able to deal with the questionable politics of Catherby.
** '''Juna:''' It seems you humans are always coming up with new political systems. This one sounds like it might need a bit more work...
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Curse of Arrav]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and so I escaped with the heart of Arrav!
** '''Juna:''' The separation of heart from man is not natural. It is good you are looking to resolve such matters.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Darkness of Hallowvale]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... I gave Safalaan the book on Haemalchemy, and he recommended me for a position on the Myreque.
** '''Juna:''' I am sure you will have many more adventures on behalf of the Myreque. Then, perhaps, you will have even more stories to tell me.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Death Plateau]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So from then on the Imperial Guard was able to access Death Plateau safely and take the trolls by surprise.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Death to the Dorgeshuun]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... Sigmund escaped again, but Zanik and I destroyed the machine and Dorgesh-Kaan was saved!
** '''Juna:''' Zanik still has her destiny to fulfil, and I have a feeling you will have a part in that.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Death on the Isle]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and so that's how I solved the case of the murder on the isle.
** '''Juna:''' Ambition is so often the death of reason. It is good you were able to find the culprit.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Defender of Varrock]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... the Shield of Arrav glowed with lightning, and Dimintheis used it to defeat the zombie army!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Demon Slayer]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So I destroyed the demon Delrith and saved Varrock!
** '''Juna:''' I remember Delrith. A most unpleasant character; I am glad he has been dispatched.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Depths of Despair]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and I returned the Royal Accord of Twill to Lord Hosidius.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Desert Treasure I]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... In the pyramid I discovered a whole new set of magic spells!
** '''Juna:''' I suggest you think about the origin of those spells. Ancient magics are not to be toyed with.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Desert Treasure II - The Fallen Empire]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and it turns out the treasure in the vault was actually the Elder Horn!
** '''Juna:''' For an artefact like that to be unleashed upon this world... Let us hope this is not the end of the story.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Devious Minds]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So it was me who accidentally brought a teleport beacon onto Entrana! But the Temple Knights are investigating so it should all be all right.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Dig Site]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and the examiner was very impressed that I had discovered an ancient altar of Zaros.
** '''Juna:''' Zaros? I had not heard that name for a thousand years even before the start of my sojourn here.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Doric's Quest]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So once I had got all the ores he wanted, Doric let me use his anvils.
** '''Juna:''' Such a small task hardly seems worthy of the term 'quest'.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Dragon Slayer I]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So with Elvarg the dragon dead, the master of the Champions' Guild let me in, and I was able to wear Rune Plate!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Dragon Slayer II]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so I slew the dragon which killed the dragonkin as well. 
** '''Player:''' Not everyone survived the fight though.
** '''Juna:''' The dragonkin once brought this world to the brink of ruin. It is good you stopped them from doing so again.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Dream Mentor]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so Cyrisus was free of his fear of combat, and he headed off to be an adventurer.
** '''Juna:''' Fear is the most insidious enemy of all.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Druidic Ritual]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So Kaqemeex taught me how to use the Herblore skill.
** '''Juna:''' A generous reward indeed.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Dwarf Cannon]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and that was how I fixed the Dwarf multicannon.
** '''Juna:''' So war still rages in the world above? Will you never tire of creating machines of destruction?
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Eadgar's Ruse]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... Eadgar's ruse was absurd, but it worked! {{Sic}} The trolls ate a fake human, and I got the herb for the druids' ritual.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Eagles' Peak]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so Nickolaus taught me how to catch a new ferret for the zoo.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Elemental Workshop I]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and once I had repaired the Elemental Workshop I was able to make an Elemental Shield.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Elemental Workshop II]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so I instilled the power of my mind into the primed bar and smithed it into an Elemental Mind Helm!
** '''Juna:''' You should be careful about meddling with your own head.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Enakhra's Lament]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and then Akthanakos and Enakhra went away to the north to continue fighting!
** '''Juna:''' A battle between two such powerful beings will take much time and unleash much energy. I hope that the natural world is not damaged in this conflict!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Enlightened Journey]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so we landed the balloon in Taverley, and Auguste thanked me for helping him get his idea off the ground.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Ernest the Chicken]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So once I had found all the parts for the machine, poor Ernest could be himself once more.
** '''Juna:''' That was a good deed. It is a terrible thing to be locked out of one's natural form.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Ethically Acquired Antiquities]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and I know they meant well, but I did have to explain to them that they couldn't just go 'borrowing' from other museums!
** '''Juna:''' Is it ever right to steal? It is a conundrum older than time, though I think in this case, the answer is clear.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Eyes of Glouphrie]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... the machine revealed that the cute creatures were actually Arposandran spies! I destroyed them, and King Narnode gave me a crystal seed that belonged to Oaknock the Engineer.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Fairytale I - Growing Pains]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So I defeated the tanglefoot and returned the Fairy Queen's Enchanted Secateurs to the Fairy Godfather.
** '''Juna:''' These fairies seem to be well versed in the powers of nature.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Fairytale II - Cure a Queen]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... the Fairy Queen awoke, and we realised that the Godfather had betrayed her!
** '''Juna:''' Politics is never straightforward.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Family Crest]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So all three parts of the family crest were reunited.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Feud]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ...So despite the failure of my original task, Ali Morrisane was very happy about his nephew's fortunes.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Fight Arena]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and I defeated General Khazard, and won the Servils their freedom!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Final Dawn]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and so it turned out that the archive was never completed. Everything Metzli did was for nothing...
** '''Juna:''' She let her greed consume her, and paid the ultimate price.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Fishing Contest]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and after I had won the fishing contest, the Dwarves let me go under White Wolf Mountain.
** '''Juna:''' Fishing? A strange test of worthiness to pass through an underground tunnel!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Forgettable Tale...]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... I think I did something with a drunken dwarf... but I can't remember what.
** '''Juna:''' You must be careful not to let drink muddle your brain!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Forsaken Tower]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and so I took the hammer to Undor and he used it to repair the Doors of Dinh.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Fremennik Exiles]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and that's how we defeated the Jormungand once and for all!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Fremennik Isles]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so I presented the head of the Troll King to the Burgher and he gave me his own helm!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Fremennik Trials]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and that was how I became an honourary member the Fremennik, and was given my Fremennik name, [Fremennik name].
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Garden of Death]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so it seems that in trying to prevent it, the Old Ones managed to cause their extinction instead.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Garden of Tranquillity]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So the garden at Varrock palace is all my work!
** '''Juna:''' It is good that you can take time from slaying and adventuring to grow a beautiful garden.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Gertrude's Cat]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ...I returned Fluffs safely to Gertrude, and then she gave me a cat of my own!
** '''Juna:''' Cats are one of the most mysterious creatures of Guthix. I hope you take your responsibility seriously.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Getting Ahead]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and so I ended up having to make a pretend head. Not exactly how I expected things to go, but at least I managed to keep my head up throughout it all!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Ghosts Ahoy]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So the people of Port Phasmatys were finally able to rest.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Giant Dwarf]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So the statue in Keldagrim was rebuilt, and I witnessed a meeting of the Consortium of mining companies.
** '''Juna:''' I have a feeling that Keldagrim will be the setting of many great adventures for you.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Goblin Diplomacy]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So the goblins ended up wearing the armour colour they had to start off with!
** '''Juna:''' Poor silly goblins! Their race had such potential, if only they could rise above their petty squabbles.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Golem]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and I had to reprogram the golem before it would believe that the demon was dead.
** '''Juna:''' I remember well the battle of Uzer.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Grand Tree]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... Glough fled like the coward he really is, and the Grand Tree was saved!
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Great Brain Robbery]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... so I defeated Mi-Gor's barrel-chested bodyguard, and the monks were saved.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Grim Tales]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and once I'd chopped down the beanstalk, Sylas let me keep Rupert's helmet.
** '''Juna:''' Your tales are often very curious, [player name].
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Hand in the Sand]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... So that was how I gave Bert a hand solving the murder and returned the wizard's head to solve the riddle of the ever full sand pits!
** '''Juna:''' A victim dies and a murderer is punished. That is balance.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Haunted Mine]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** '''Player:''' ... and from the legendary crystals I cut a salve shard to fight the undead.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[Hazeel Cult]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
** {{tcond|If the player stopped the cultists:}}
*** '''Player:''' ... So that was how I foiled the cultists in their plan to resurrect Hazeel.
** {{tcond|If the player helped the cultists:}}
*** '''Player:''' ... So that was how I helped return Hazeel to his followers.
** '''Juna:''' So the vile Mahjarrat still walk the earth above? Then Zamorak's defeat was not as thorough as I had thought.
** {{tact|continues}}
* {{topt|cond=If [[The Heart of Darkness]] is completed:|Dialogue {{+=|number|1|echo=1}}}}
